#floodfinder
  #abovefold
    %h1 Is it Flooding?
    %p#privacy
      This application uses geolocation; it sends your coordinates to
      a central service, where they may be logged and tracked. If you
      do not want this, click "Deny" when it asks for your location.
    #floodzone{style: 'display: none'}
      %h2.flooding
        {{#flooding}} Yes {{/flooding}}
        {{^flooding}} No {{/flooding}}
      %p.desc
        {{#flooding}} It's probably flooding. {{/flooding}}
        {{^flooding}} It's probably not flooding. {{/flooding}}
      %p.rain 
        {{^flooding}} Only {{/flooding}}
        {{#round}}{{ rain_estimate }}{{/round}} in. of rain today.
      %h3 FEMA Information
      %p.fema
        FEMA flood zone
        %span.zone_name< {{ zone.name }}:
        %span.zone_designation {{ zone_designation }}
  #belowfold
    #localgeo{style: 'display: none'}
      %h3 You're at:
      %dl
        %dt Longitude
        %dd {{#biground}}{{ coords.longitude }}{{/biground}}
        %dt Latitude
        %dd {{#biground}}{{ coords.latitude }}{{/biground}}
        %dt Horizontal Accuracy
        %dd {{ coords.accuracy }}m
    #about
      %h3 About:
      %p
        Is it Flooding was made at Hack For Change: Miami, 
        the weekend of June 1-2, 2013 in Miami.
        
      %p
        Built by 
        = link_to 'Bryce Kerley', 'https://twitter.com/bonzoesc'
        using Ruby, Rails, PostgreSQL, and PostGIS.
        Source code is available on 
        = link_to 'GitHub.', 'https://github.com/bkerley/flood/'

      %h3 Data Sources:
      %ul
        %li
          Rainfall data from the
          = link_to 'http://water.weather.gov/precip/download.php' do
            Advanced Hydrologic Prediction Service
          part of the National Weather Service.
        %li
          FEMA Flood Zone data from 
          = link_to 'http://gisweb.miamidade.gov/GISSelfServices/GeographicData/MDGeographicData.html' do
            Miami-Dade County GIS.
          = link_to 'http://gisweb.miamidade.gov/GISSelfServices/Data/HTML/FEMAFloodZone.htm' do
            Flood Zone Metadata is available.
    #meta
      #nobueno{style: 'display: none'}
        Couldn't activate geolocation.
        %strong USING SAMPLE DATA
    #spinnaz{style: 'display: none'}
      ridin' spinnaz
